INSERT INTO `article_description` VALUES ('67', 'en', 'IFRC Provincial Indexes', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<strong>The Vietnam Geographical Economic Indexes series</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The Vietnam geographical economic indexes are designed and calculated based on the data of companies listed on stock exchanges, has its head office located in that geographic area. These indexes are calculated in proportion to market capitalisation, in the price and total return version; and conversion of different currencies (VND, USD, EUR, JPY).</p>\r\n', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	At the national level, Vietnam is trying to improve its competitiveness and international integration. Within the scope of local, regional leaders (province, city) were also eager to reform and develop policies and strategies for local economic development. The competition is silent, drastic and effective but has not been evaluated completely. PAPI (The Vietnam Provincial Governance and Public Administration Performance Index) and PCI (Provincial Competitiveness Index) biased towards measuring policy effectiveness. Therefore, Intelligent Financial Research &amp; Consulting (IFRC) initiatives to create a Vietnam geographical economic index measuring the economic efficiency of provinces, cities and regions in Vietnam.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	The Vietnam Geographical Economic Indexes series are including :</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The Provincial Indexes (actually 25 biggest provinces and cities, only provinces having at least 5 listed companies are calculated)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The Regional Indexes (6 regions).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '');
