INSERT INTO `article_description` VALUES ('151', 'en', 'BOOK REVIEW: Derivatives: Principles and Practice', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Stephen Figlewski </strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Journal of Derivatives</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>Summer 2010, Vol. 17, No. 4: pp. 79-81 </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	Rangarajan Sundaram and Sanjiv Das have just published a new textbook on derivatives, Derivatives: Principles and Practice. Sanjiv is a co-editor of The Journal of Derivatives, as was Raghu until fairly recently, so while it was in process one hoped (and expected) that their book would be very good. We review their excellent new contribution to the derivatives bookshelf here.</p>\r\n', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	A new textbook by Rangarajan Sundaram and Sanjiv Das, Derivatives: Principles and Practice, published by McGraw-Hill Irwin, has just made its appearance. This book should be of great interest to The Journal of Derivatives&rsquo; readers, because both Sundaram and Das have served as co-editors of the Journal (Das is serving currently). It is of particular interest to me personally, since in addition to being close friends with both authors, Raghu Sundaram is also a colleague at the New York University Stern School. We teach the same course on futures and options, to the same population of MBA students and advanced undergraduates. A lot of the material in the book is drawn from Raghu&rsquo;s class notes, and since he consistently receives among the highest teacher ratings in the school, he is obviously doing something&mdash;a lot of things&mdash;right.</p>\r\n', '', '');
